NUMBER 1764
CHANNEL 82
NAME Deep Realms, Blood of Andor
REGION 2
DEEPCAVE
DROPLOC 1769
FIXED_LIGHT
MINEC
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
You stand at a narrow outcrop before the edge of a gargantuan chasm, beholding an awesome vision of nature's might and fury. Beneath you, through a haze of thick, putrid fumes, the Blood of Andor churns interminably, a veritable river of fire. The low roar of molten rock echoes through the cavern and its glow paints all in a deep, crimson hue. The unbearable heat makes your curse mortal flesh and wish for the simple gifts of cool air and refreshing water.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 1507
EXIT W 1761
IFVERB SEARCH -1
ECHO PLAYER A quick search of the outcrop reveals that a dangerous climb could be attempted on a ledge that slopes upward along the side of the chasm.
ENDIF
IFVERB JUMP -1
	ECHO OTHERS %N jumps into the chaos towards oblivion.
	ECHO PLAYER You jump straight into oblivion.
	MOVE 1769
ENDIF
IFVERB GO 0
	ECHO PLAYER You will have to climb that.
	CLEARVERB
ENDIF
IFVERB CLIMB 0
	CLEARVERB
	IFVAR SKILL5 < 1
		ECHO PLAYER Having no skill in climbing whatsoever, you decide that leading such a climb would be folly.
	ELSE
		EQUAL ROUNDTIME 10
		SKILLCHECK 5 -30 DUMMY1
		IFVAR DUMMY1 >= 0
			ECHO GROUP You carefully make your way up the ledge, realizing at last that this climb could never be attempted in reverse. There is no turning back now.
			ECHO OTHGROUP %P makes the careful trek up the ledge.
			MOVEGROUP 1770
			AFFECT 1770
			ECHO OTHGROUP %P arrives after making a careful trek up the ledge.
		ENDIF
		IFVAR DUMMY1 < -75
			ECHO PLAYER You start the treacherous climb, but your footholds begin to crumble!
			IFVAR SKILL5 < 5
				ECHO PLAYER You slip and fall into the chasm, wondering in your final moments of life if you would have been better off knowing how to climb a little better...
                                ECHO OTHERS You watch as %n, begins to make their way up the ledge, but gasp in horror as %s looses %h footing and tumbles to a fiery grave! You are glad you weren't following.
				MOVE 1769
			ELSE
				ECHO PLAYER You retreat swiftly, realizing that it was only your calm and skill that saved you from certain doom.
                                ECHO OTHERS %P begins to climb up the ledge, but the footholds begin to give way! Thinking quickly as only a master climber can, %n tracks a new route back to the bottom of the ledge.
			ENDIF
		ELSE
			IFVAR DUMMY1 < -40
				ECHO PLAYER You make your way up the ledge, but your footing becomes unsteady! A rock becomes dislodged, tumbling its way into the chasm. You hastily retreat, breathing a sigh of relief that you survived.
                                ECHO OTHERS %P makes their way up the ledge, but %n becomes unsure of %h footing and is forced to retreat to the bottom of the ledge.
			ELSE
				ECHO PLAYER You make your way up the ledge, but fail to find any further footholds or handholds. Alas, you are forced to backtrack to your starting point.
                                ECHO OTHERS %P makes their way up the ledge, but fails to find any further footholds or handholds. Alas, %s is forced to backtrack to the beginning.
			ENDIF
		ENDIF
	ENDIF
ENDIF
