NUMBER 1370
REGION 2
NAME Kragenholm, town gates
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Looming up towards the ceiling of the cavern, huge titanium double doors stand guard before an entrance. The gleaming doors almost shimmer with a life as they reflect and intensify the light refracted from millions of gems imbedded in the cavern walls. A locking bar made of solid truesteel further reinforces the thick door. The sounds of people, laughter, voices and children echo through the cavern in a warm cachaphoney.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MONSTER_GROUP 40
DEEPCAVE
CHANNEL 82
FIXED_LIGHT
ITEM 0 350 ADJ1=163 ADJ2=328 ADJ3=97 VAL2=1778
EXTEND 0 with a locking bar of solid truesteel
EXIT W 1371
IFVERB RECALL -1
	ECHO PLAYER When you think about it, you realize that with no night or day, the townspeople could be up and about at just about anytime.
ENDIF
IFVERB GAZE -1
	ECHO PLAYER You see what is apparently a main street of avenue running to the west. It is actually like a huge tunnel bored out of the rock. On either side structures are built out onto the street. Given their lack of depth, one assumes that much of their interior space is dug in further out of the rock. Imbedded gems and veins of precious metals glitter in the torchlight from millions of places in the rock walls. One could call this an emerald city, or diamond city, or opal, or sardonyx...
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PULL 0
	CLEARVERB
	IFVAR ROUNDTIME > 0
		STRCVT 0 ROUNDTIME
		ECHO PLAYER [Wait %0 seconds...]
	ENDIF
	IFVAR ROUNDTIME = 0
		IFITEM 1 OPEN
			ECHO PLAYER You pull on the doors, but they will not open any further.
			ECHO OTHERS %N pulls on the doors, but they will not open any further.
		ENDIF
		IFITEM 0 CLOSED
			EQUAL ROUNDTIME 15
			ECHO PLAYER You tug against the doors...%c [Round: 15 sec]
			ECHO OTHERS %n tugs against the doors...
			RANDOM DUMMY1 1 100 0
			ADD DUMMY1 STR
			IFVAR DUMMY1 > 150
				ECHO PLAYER The doors creak open slowly.
				ECHO OTHERS %N slowly pulls the doors open.
				OPEN 0
				AFFECT 1378
				OPEN 1
			ENDIF
			IFVAR DUMMY1 < 151
				ECHO ALL Nothing happens.
			ENDIF
		ENDIF
	ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB OPEN 0
	CLEARVERB
	IFITEM 0 OPEN
		ECHO PLAYER It is already open.
	ELSE
		ECHO PLAYER You try and open the door, but it won't budge. Maybe if you pulled.
	ENDIF
ENDIF
